And I wanna tell you, that is really,

00:52:17.610 --> 00:52:19.331
really good news.

00:52:19.351 --> 00:52:20.251
So here we are.

00:52:21.320 --> 00:52:25.443
We recognize that Dowd completed the first

00:52:25.503 --> 00:52:26.643
phase of the mission.

00:52:27.244 --> 00:52:30.226
He was responsible for fulfilling the

00:52:30.266 --> 00:52:32.389
spring Miqrah, Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym.

00:52:32.869 --> 00:52:35.490
And that we know that Yahowah had a

00:52:35.650 --> 00:52:38.233
major plan for Dowd,

00:52:38.273 --> 00:52:39.873
not only in his first of three lives

00:52:39.934 --> 00:52:41.534
and acquiring Jerusalem,

00:52:41.596 --> 00:52:42.896
acquiring the Temple Mount,

00:52:43.416 --> 00:52:44.617
protecting God's people,

00:52:45.342 --> 00:52:47.164
uniting Israel,

00:52:47.565 --> 00:52:50.588
writing these marvelous Psalms so that we

00:52:50.628 --> 00:52:53.090
might know who God is, what He's offering,

00:52:53.110 --> 00:52:54.451
what He's expecting in return,

00:52:54.471 --> 00:52:56.853
and the role that Dowd would play to

00:52:56.913 --> 00:52:58.454
enable the benefits of the covenant.

00:52:58.954 --> 00:53:00.735
And then all of the word pictures and

00:53:00.775 --> 00:53:01.637
the Mashal,

00:53:01.996 --> 00:53:04.278
they give us such wonderful insights into

00:53:04.318 --> 00:53:06.121
the mindset of not only Dowd,

00:53:06.161 --> 00:53:08.523
but of Yahowah as well.

00:53:09.628 --> 00:53:10.068
and of those,

00:53:10.088 --> 00:53:11.548
the cast of characters that's going to be

00:53:11.608 --> 00:53:13.909
working with them.

00:53:14.030 --> 00:53:15.989
And so we have so much that we

00:53:16.010 --> 00:53:18.010
should be grateful for in his first life.

00:53:18.050 --> 00:53:19.692
And then in his second life,

00:53:20.472 --> 00:53:22.273
he made it possible for us to live

00:53:22.293 --> 00:53:24.614
forever, for us to inherit the covenant,

00:53:24.653 --> 00:53:28.335
for us to be enriched and empowered by

00:53:28.394 --> 00:53:30.356
God, to be adopted into God's family,

00:53:30.416 --> 00:53:32.215
to live forever, to be perfected.

00:53:32.936 --> 00:53:34.317
This is a pretty extraordinary thing.

00:53:34.336 --> 00:53:35.818
And he comes back in his third life

00:53:36.137 --> 00:53:38.338
with all of the responsibility on his

00:53:38.378 --> 00:53:38.759
shoulders.

00:53:39.199 --> 00:53:41.460
He's king forevermore.

00:53:41.501 --> 00:53:44.302
He is God's influence in our presence.

00:53:44.322 --> 00:53:46.764
That's why he's called Elion,

00:53:47.284 --> 00:53:50.465
which means the very hand of God Almighty.

00:53:52.327 --> 00:53:54.588
His throne is actually the mercy seat of

00:53:54.628 --> 00:53:55.650
the Ark of the Covenant,

00:53:56.070 --> 00:53:57.311
and it will endure forever.

00:53:58.150 --> 00:53:59.632
He is the tree of life.

00:53:59.692 --> 00:54:03.014
So God had a lot to say about

00:54:03.333 --> 00:54:05.516
his relationship and the contribution of

00:54:05.576 --> 00:54:07.496
his beloved son, Dowd.

00:54:08.547 --> 00:54:13.251
And it all reminds us of Dowd's craving

00:54:13.311 --> 00:54:14.992
for knowledge and inspiration,

00:54:15.692 --> 00:54:18.333
but also his humanity.

00:54:18.715 --> 00:54:22.498
Dowd was in so many ways like us.

00:54:23.798 --> 00:54:26.300
He was a man who was learning on

00:54:26.320 --> 00:54:26.760
the job.

00:54:27.481 --> 00:54:29.382
He was a man who made mistakes and

00:54:29.463 --> 00:54:31.364
got up and dusted himself off and said,

00:54:31.403 --> 00:54:31.724
all right,

00:54:32.574 --> 00:54:33.494
Let's go it again.

00:54:33.875 --> 00:54:34.894
We can do better next time.

00:54:36.076 --> 00:54:37.836
He was a man of great compassion,

00:54:37.876 --> 00:54:40.197
of great courage, of great intellect,

00:54:40.318 --> 00:54:41.918
exceedingly articulate,

00:54:42.438 --> 00:54:46.119
and yet fully human with all of the

00:54:46.240 --> 00:54:48.402
kinds of aches and pains that we deal

00:54:48.422 --> 00:54:49.961
with on a daily basis.

00:54:50.001 --> 00:54:54.083
He began the sixth of his songs,

00:54:54.123 --> 00:54:56.005
the Mizmowr, with these words.

00:54:56.905 --> 00:55:01.427
The enduring leader, La ha Natasha.

00:55:02.331 --> 00:55:04.172
to approach and on behalf of the

00:55:04.253 --> 00:55:06.952
everlasting conductor and the majestic

00:55:06.992 --> 00:55:09.873
director who endeavors to lead and is

00:55:09.954 --> 00:55:13.155
preeminent and distinguished forever.

00:55:13.215 --> 00:55:17.195
So nachash is actually a verb and thus

00:55:17.356 --> 00:55:20.536
actionable in the text as modified by the

00:55:21.016 --> 00:55:22.597
Peale participle.

00:55:22.898 --> 00:55:24.777
And as a participle,

00:55:24.918 --> 00:55:28.199
it is very much like the infinitive where

00:55:28.795 --> 00:55:30.635
The verb is also a noun.

00:55:30.675 --> 00:55:33.835
So it is, nachash is an actionable title,

00:55:34.275 --> 00:55:34.815
if you will.

00:55:35.536 --> 00:55:36.456
This director,

00:55:36.675 --> 00:55:42.396
this conductor is actively engaged.

00:55:42.476 --> 00:55:45.237
And it says, to the nachash,

00:55:45.498 --> 00:55:47.938
accompanied by stringed instruments.

00:55:47.978 --> 00:55:48.338
In other words,

00:55:48.358 --> 00:55:51.018
these are lyrics to a song that has

00:55:51.079 --> 00:55:51.478
melody.

00:55:52.518 --> 00:55:56.739
Above and beyond the eighth octave note.

00:55:58.018 --> 00:56:00.900
scale for eternity for heaven and beyond

00:56:02.041 --> 00:56:06.184
from Shemini and Shemoneh eighth and

00:56:06.304 --> 00:56:09.746
infinite in time and relative to the

00:56:09.806 --> 00:56:13.969
spiritual realm it's well we know Shamaym

00:56:14.070 --> 00:56:16.992
is a seven-dimensional construct but it is

00:56:17.112 --> 00:56:20.454
infinite in time and there is i mean

00:56:21.411 --> 00:56:23.713
To say that Shamaym is seven-dimensional,

00:56:23.793 --> 00:56:25.335
because that's Yahowah's favorite number,

00:56:25.355 --> 00:56:26.615
six plus one equals seven,

00:56:27.195 --> 00:56:28.818
and we know that the universe is

00:56:29.097 --> 00:56:29.838
six-dimensional,

00:56:30.699 --> 00:56:32.802
this takes us to the point we would

00:56:32.862 --> 00:56:34.963
naturally conclude that Shamaym is the

00:56:35.043 --> 00:56:35.764
seventh dimension.

00:56:36.224 --> 00:56:39.467
But it doesn't have to remain that way.

00:56:41.195 --> 00:56:44.458
Yahowah could well be eight dimensions to

00:56:44.498 --> 00:56:46.900
have created a seventh dimension spiritual

00:56:46.940 --> 00:56:47.181
realm.

00:56:47.840 --> 00:56:50.884
And he could be more than eight dimensions

00:56:50.923 --> 00:56:51.324
as well.

00:56:51.905 --> 00:56:54.748
And could take us even beyond the seventh

00:56:54.768 --> 00:56:57.210
dimension of Shamaym, of heaven.

00:56:57.849 --> 00:56:59.391
So it's something to think about.

00:56:59.431 --> 00:57:01.193
This was the introduction to,

00:57:01.434 --> 00:57:02.735
the dedication, if you will,

00:57:03.496 --> 00:57:05.898
of the sixth Mizmowr psalm.

00:57:12.434 --> 00:57:12.534
Now,

00:57:12.554 --> 00:57:16.498
this is one of only three times that

00:57:17.840 --> 00:57:20.141
Shemoneh, the eighth,

00:57:20.862 --> 00:57:22.083
appears in the text,

00:57:23.164 --> 00:57:26.347
each in reference to the instrumentation

00:57:26.527 --> 00:57:27.248
for a song.

00:57:28.108 --> 00:57:32.552
And since it is clearly related to Shemoneh

00:57:32.733 --> 00:57:33.572
 , eight,

00:57:34.534 --> 00:57:38.257
scholars typically consider Shemoneh to

00:57:38.277 --> 00:57:39.978
be the eighth octave.

00:57:40.802 --> 00:57:41.222
In fact,

00:57:41.782 --> 00:57:44.644
the English word octave is based upon the

00:57:44.724 --> 00:57:48.387
Latin word for eight, octo.

00:57:49.847 --> 00:57:52.570
The issue with limiting it to this

00:57:52.771 --> 00:57:56.112
singular expression is that a harp can

00:57:56.213 --> 00:57:58.934
only play six and a half octaves,

00:57:59.275 --> 00:57:59.795
not eight,

00:58:00.596 --> 00:58:03.077
and its range exceeds that of other

00:58:03.257 --> 00:58:04.219
stringed instruments.

00:58:05.358 --> 00:58:08.541
Further, our most accomplished singers

00:58:09.621 --> 00:58:13.342
have a four octave range with the eighth

00:58:13.543 --> 00:58:17.585
octave residing at the upward limit of

00:58:17.605 --> 00:58:22.847
what people can even hear.

00:58:22.947 --> 00:58:25.128
It's the beyond.

00:58:27.068 --> 00:58:30.530
When we consider the scale of eight in

00:58:30.590 --> 00:58:32.530
harmony with Yahowah's nomenclature,

00:58:33.251 --> 00:58:35.592
we find several thought provoking ideas.

00:58:36.447 --> 00:58:39.309
The eighth day of Sukah is an ode

00:58:39.389 --> 00:58:41.731
to eternal life with God in heaven.

00:58:42.311 --> 00:58:45.014
And in this regard, the word for eight,

00:58:45.514 --> 00:58:46.195
Shemini,

00:58:46.755 --> 00:58:49.657
is remarkably similar to the Hebrew word

00:58:49.677 --> 00:58:50.978
for heaven, Shamaym.

00:58:51.920 --> 00:58:52.739
And third,

00:58:52.780 --> 00:58:56.943
there are seven notes in an octave, A,

00:58:56.983 --> 00:58:59.806
B, C, D, E, F, and G.

00:59:01.425 --> 00:59:03.885
audibly affirming that Yahowah's plan,

00:59:04.606 --> 00:59:09.266
one which reverberates throughout time,

00:59:09.306 --> 00:59:13.807
goes beyond the seventh and into the

00:59:13.887 --> 00:59:15.148
eighth octave.

00:59:16.867 --> 00:59:17.427
Therefore,

00:59:18.469 --> 00:59:21.168
I suspect that Dowd is dedicating this

00:59:21.208 --> 00:59:24.849
song to Yahowah in recognition of his

00:59:24.909 --> 00:59:28.010
desire to spend his eternity in his

00:59:28.070 --> 00:59:29.231
Father's company in heaven.

00:59:30.199 --> 00:59:31.940
He could even be saying something that I

00:59:31.960 --> 00:59:33.442
had not considered previously.

00:59:34.463 --> 00:59:37.005
And that is that Yahowah,

00:59:37.445 --> 00:59:39.467
who I've always assumed was at least seven

00:59:39.507 --> 00:59:41.449
dimensional because he created a six

00:59:41.489 --> 00:59:43.291
dimensional universe and you have to be a

00:59:43.331 --> 00:59:47.855
dimension beyond that which you create for

00:59:47.914 --> 00:59:50.918
you to build something that is of such

00:59:50.978 --> 00:59:51.318
scale.

00:59:54.139 --> 00:59:55.800
in this, you know, for example,

00:59:56.141 --> 00:59:57.282
we can build buildings,

00:59:57.543 --> 00:59:58.684
but they're out of the things that are

00:59:58.724 --> 00:59:59.606
already here.

00:59:59.927 --> 01:00:01.168
When you're creating something from

01:00:01.307 --> 01:00:01.668
nothing,

01:00:01.929 --> 01:00:05.393
you have to be a dimension beyond it.

01:00:05.474 --> 01:00:05.653
Where

01:00:06.137 --> 01:00:06.458
You know,

01:00:06.478 --> 01:00:10.780
there's the old cartoon that says, well,

01:00:10.800 --> 01:00:11.320
you know, God,

01:00:11.340 --> 01:00:12.942
we don't need you anymore because science

01:00:12.981 --> 01:00:15.182
has figured out how to conceive life.

01:00:15.744 --> 01:00:16.664
By the way, it's not true.

01:00:16.704 --> 01:00:18.425
Science doesn't have a clue as about the

01:00:18.485 --> 01:00:19.226
conception of life.

01:00:19.246 --> 01:00:21.786
They don't even understand what a soul is.

01:00:22.507 --> 01:00:24.248
But the fact is, OK,

01:00:24.268 --> 01:00:25.869
so they're having a conversation.

01:00:25.969 --> 01:00:26.849
We don't need more.

01:00:26.909 --> 01:00:28.650
We can create life just from dirt and

01:00:28.670 --> 01:00:29.371
that sort of thing.

01:00:29.411 --> 01:00:31.132
And so God says, OK, prove it.

01:00:31.733 --> 01:00:32.974
And so the scientist begins,

01:00:33.014 --> 01:00:34.574
he gets some dirt together and says, no,

01:00:34.594 --> 01:00:36.036
no, no, get your own dirt.

01:00:36.076 --> 01:00:39.137
And so this is really the point of

01:00:40.278 --> 01:00:42.099
if you're going to create a universe that

01:00:42.179 --> 01:00:44.481
is where you are responsible for

01:00:44.581 --> 01:00:45.503
everything in it,

01:00:46.063 --> 01:00:47.945
then you need to be a dimension beyond

01:00:48.005 --> 01:00:48.085
it.

01:00:49.405 --> 01:00:52.668
And so with Shamaym playing such an

01:00:52.728 --> 01:00:54.748
important role and it being the dimension

01:00:54.789 --> 01:00:57.471
beyond the physical universe and it

01:00:57.670 --> 01:00:59.333
therefore being seven dimensions,

01:01:00.052 --> 01:01:00.954
wouldn't we naturally

01:01:02.599 --> 01:01:03.059
assume,

01:01:03.561 --> 01:01:06.884
credibly conclude that Yahowah would be a

01:01:06.923 --> 01:01:08.987
dimension beyond that and therefore eight

01:01:09.027 --> 01:01:09.447
dimensional.

01:01:11.730 --> 01:01:14.974
I think there's every possibility of that

01:01:15.014 --> 01:01:15.494
being true.

01:01:17.275 --> 01:01:19.818
And this of course means that God is

01:01:19.938 --> 01:01:20.179
not

01:01:22.001 --> 01:01:26.405
limiting us to what we currently know.

01:01:26.806 --> 01:01:29.487
And so Dowd is dedicating the song to

01:01:29.527 --> 01:01:33.451
Yahowah in recognition that we will enjoy

01:01:33.550 --> 01:01:35.532
an eternity together in his Father's

01:01:35.572 --> 01:01:36.313
company in heaven.

01:01:36.612 --> 01:01:37.454
And that

01:01:37.795 --> 01:01:40.438
There could be even an opportunity beyond

01:01:40.458 --> 01:01:40.739
that.

01:01:41.380 --> 01:01:43.902
And he realizes that God is not pleased

01:01:43.922 --> 01:01:45.784
with the conduct of men on earth.

01:01:46.204 --> 01:01:48.085
And he certainly wasn't pleased with the

01:01:48.106 --> 01:01:49.708
conduct of Adam and Chawah.

01:01:49.768 --> 01:01:52.851
And clearly hasn't been pleased with the

01:01:52.891 --> 01:01:55.393
conduct of humanity in general and with

01:01:55.474 --> 01:01:56.934
Israel in particular.

01:01:57.735 --> 01:01:59.797
And that the conditions will be far better

01:02:00.539 --> 01:02:01.719
in the next life.

01:02:02.833 --> 01:02:02.932
Now,

01:02:02.972 --> 01:02:05.215
the sentiment expressed in this opening

01:02:05.255 --> 01:02:08.117
statement of Dowd's song is central to our

01:02:08.217 --> 01:02:10.519
understanding as it is universally

01:02:10.659 --> 01:02:11.201
ignored.

01:02:11.880 --> 01:02:14.302
The purpose of the Beryth, the covenant,

01:02:14.983 --> 01:02:18.286
and of the Towrah guidance and teaching is

01:02:18.646 --> 01:02:19.248
yakach,

01:02:20.188 --> 01:02:22.670
persuasively demonstrated and proven

01:02:23.110 --> 01:02:23.672
through Dowd.

01:02:24.485 --> 01:02:27.226
He is the antidote to rabbinic Judaism and

01:02:27.246 --> 01:02:28.489
to Pauline Christianity.

01:02:28.989 --> 01:02:31.251
He demonstrates that the Towrah,

01:02:31.570 --> 01:02:33.132
rather than condemning,

01:02:33.632 --> 01:02:36.215
perfects the imperfect so that we can

01:02:36.255 --> 01:02:38.356
become beloved sons and daughters of

01:02:38.396 --> 01:02:38.858
Yahowah.

01:02:40.199 --> 01:02:42.900
Here is the opening line of the sixth

01:02:42.940 --> 01:02:43.340
mizmowr.

01:02:43.360 --> 01:02:49.367
Yahowah, you consistently prove your case.

01:02:51.596 --> 01:02:53.436
with pervasive arguments,

01:02:53.916 --> 01:02:59.260
which vindicate me and acquit through me.

01:03:02.583 --> 01:03:04.545
You use evidence and reason,

01:03:05.684 --> 01:03:08.126
engaging in rational dialogue with me,

01:03:08.706 --> 01:03:11.268
making decisions and resolving disputes

01:03:11.329 --> 01:03:11.809
through me,

01:03:12.349 --> 01:03:15.311
demonstrating that you and I are right.

01:03:16.710 --> 01:03:17.590
was written in the Hifl,

01:03:17.990 --> 01:03:21.132
which means that God is the subject,

01:03:21.632 --> 01:03:24.855
is making this possible for Dowd,

01:03:24.954 --> 01:03:28.416
and actually engaging with Dowd as if he

01:03:28.436 --> 01:03:29.657
were a secondary subject.

01:03:30.637 --> 01:03:31.237
Imperfect,

01:03:31.617 --> 01:03:34.699
which means this has ongoing implications

01:03:34.800 --> 01:03:35.561
over time.

01:03:36.760 --> 01:03:37.621
And Jusuf,

01:03:37.641 --> 01:03:39.583
which is an expression of third person

01:03:39.603 --> 01:03:39.682
life.

01:03:41.282 --> 01:03:44.744
So Yah is continually enabling Dowd to

01:03:44.804 --> 01:03:46.664
engage in the process of rational

01:03:46.704 --> 01:03:50.326
discourse within the parameters of free

01:03:50.365 --> 01:03:50.606
will.

01:03:51.385 --> 01:03:52.266
I love Hebrew.

01:03:52.686 --> 01:03:54.987
Hebrew grammar is just so utterly

01:03:55.987 --> 01:03:59.509
spectacular and so enlightening that

01:03:59.768 --> 01:04:03.371
translating from the oldest text,

01:04:04.505 --> 01:04:07.090
is tremendously rewarding and even for

01:04:07.110 --> 01:04:08.974
those who would say well i read and

01:04:09.014 --> 01:04:10.876
speak hebrew i don't need a translation oh

01:04:10.916 --> 01:04:11.356
yes you do

01:04:12.548 --> 01:04:13.969
Because, first of all,

01:04:14.409 --> 01:04:18.052
modern Hebrew bears actually only a

01:04:18.713 --> 01:04:21.434
fleeting resemblance to the Hebrew of the

01:04:21.554 --> 01:04:21.934
Towrah.

01:04:22.936 --> 01:04:27.177
It is far more shaded and contoured by

01:04:27.237 --> 01:04:30.981
the Talmud and by English than it is

01:04:31.101 --> 01:04:34.083
by the original vocabulary of the Towrah.

01:04:34.603 --> 01:04:38.364
These interesting moods play no role going

01:04:38.385 --> 01:04:39.065
forward in Judaism.

01:04:39.726 --> 01:04:40.327
In Hebrew,

01:04:40.347 --> 01:04:44.192
they've gone back to the system of verbs

01:04:44.231 --> 01:04:45.893
being stuck in time, past, present,

01:04:45.932 --> 01:04:46.434
or future,

01:04:46.474 --> 01:04:49.918
as opposed to the idea of constrained in

01:04:49.978 --> 01:04:53.802
time or unlimited in time and of the

01:04:54.242 --> 01:04:57.146
volitional moods and of the stems,

01:04:57.186 --> 01:04:57.365
which...

01:05:00.603 --> 01:05:03.666
describe the relationship between the

01:05:03.706 --> 01:05:06.208
subject and object of the sentence

01:05:06.248 --> 01:05:07.208
pursuant to the verb.

01:05:07.730 --> 01:05:08.951
And so all of these things,

01:05:09.690 --> 01:05:11.452
doing these amplified translations,

01:05:11.632 --> 01:05:13.094
I can share with you so you have

01:05:13.114 --> 01:05:15.076
a much better appreciation

01:05:15.797 --> 01:05:17.157
of what is being communicated.

01:05:17.597 --> 01:05:18.960
So with all of the chit-chat,

01:05:18.980 --> 01:05:19.980
let me go back to the beginning.

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:22.041
We can pick up our pace in this.

01:05:22.521 --> 01:05:22.902
Yahowah,

